еперь - четвёртая из пяти крупнейших стран LatAm.\n\nИрония не в том что пришли. В том что пришли первыми - с худшими условиями на рынке.\n\nОдин шанс на ЧМ-трафик. Один.\n\n@vipcare_io", "image_html": null}], "linkedin_post": {"text": "LINKEDIN POST:\n\nStake just got a government permit in Mexico. With a 50% tax rate.\n\nFive weeks before Mexico's World Cup opener at Estadio Azteca, Stake went live at stake.mx - operating through local license agent Uno Capali because SEGOB doesn't issue permits directly to new entrants. The same platform that built its entire brand on operating outside licensed frameworks is now going fully regulated in Latin America's second-largest gambling market.\n\nThis matters for VIP operations beyond the headline. Stake now has a presence in four of the five most-populated LatAm countries, bringing a VIP rakeback program that players already know and trust - in a market where traditional operators are still figuring out local player behavior.\n\nThe signal: the gray-to-regulated migration isn't slowing down. It's accelerating, and it's bringing Stake's playbook into your regulated markets. The competition for high-value LatAm players just got more sophisticated.\n\nBest-in-class VIP programs won't compete on rakeback percentages. They'll compete on experience and trust - which Stake has spent years building.\n\n#iGaming #VIPRetention #CasinoOperations #PlayerExperience"}}